claim: The Comics Code Authority (CCA) was granted dictatorial powers over comic book content by the Comics Magazine Association of America.
premise_source_doc_sentence: The Comics Code Authority  (  CCA  )  was formed in 1954 by the Comics Magazine Association of America as an alternative to government regulation , to allow the comic publishers to self-regulate the content of comic books in the United States .
